---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Wordmark from '../components/Wordmark.astro';
import Squiggle from '../components/Squiggle.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About — OddlyWiredCo"
  description="An ADHD brand made by an ADHD person. We name the parts nobody else is brave enough to put on a mug. UK-printed, neurodivergent-first, no toxic positivity."
>
  <!-- Fold 1: Hero (Ink) -->
  <section class="fold dark about-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <Wordmark size="sm" variant="darkmode"/>
      <div class="meta">about / who's behind this</div>
      <h1 class="h-mono lg">an adhd brand<br>made by an adhd person.</h1>
      <Squiggle variant="sine" width="50%"/>
      <p class="hero-sub">we name the parts of adhd nobody else is brave enough to put on a mug.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Fold 2: Hi, I'm Mads (Bone) -->
  <section class="fold light">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="meta">01 / hi, i'm mads</div>
      <h2 class="h-mono md">i started this after my diagnosis<br>in my thirties.</h2>
      <p class="body">
        I realised two things at once. One: a lot of my life suddenly made sense.
        Two: most of the products marketed at people like me were either clinical and joyless,
        or built around the idea that ADHD is a quirky productivity superpower if you just hustle harder.
      </p>
      <p class="body">
        Neither of those felt like my actual experience. The actual experience is funnier,
        messier, more tender, and a lot more specific than that. So I started making the things
        I wished existed when I got diagnosed.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Fold 3: Who this is for (Ink) -->
  <section class="fold dark">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="meta">02 / who this is for</div>
      <h2 class="h-mono md">the late-diagnosed.<br>the audhd ones.<br>the ones who slipped through.</h2>
      <p class="body">
        OddlyWiredCo is built for the late-diagnosed adults, the AuDHD ones, the ADHD women who slipped through every
        screening as kids, the ADHD parents raising ADHD kids, and anyone who has ever sat in a chair for forty minutes
        trying to start a task they actually wanted to do.
      </p>
      <p class="body">
        If "I thought I was just bad at being a person, turns out I'm neurodivergent" landed somewhere
        in your gut — you are in the right shop.
      </p>
      <div class="pullquote">
        this is an adhd-only brand by design.<br>
        no general productivity merch.<br>
        no inspirational quotes.<br>
        no toxic positivity.<br>
        one niche, full commitment.
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Fold 4: What we make (Bone) -->
  <section class="fold light">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="meta">03 / what we make</div>
      <h2 class="h-mono md">three things,<br>all neurodivergent.</h2>
      <p class="body">
        Humour and identity mugs and prints. Digital planners and tools designed for executive-function reality
        (not the "wake up at 5am and journal" version). Seasonal drops around moments like Mental Health Awareness
        Month, perimenopause overlap, and late-diagnosis anniversaries.
      </p>
      <p class="body">
        Every product targets a specific neurodivergent moment. Masking fatigue. Time blindness. Object permanence.
        The 2am doom-scroll. The hyperfocus spiral. Rejection sensitivity. The bits that do not make it into
        mainstream "ADHD content" because they are too honest.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Fold 5: How designs are made (Ink) -->
  <section class="fold dark">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="meta">04 / how designs are made</div>
      <h2 class="h-mono md">ai-assisted.<br>human-finalised.<br>told you so up front.</h2>
      <p class="body">
        Honestly: I use AI tools as part of the design process. I generate layout drafts, explore type and colour
        variations, and speed up the production side using AI. Every design is then reviewed, edited, voiced, and
        finalised by me as a human. The taste, the lines, the choices about what to say and what not to say — those are mine.
      </p>
      <p class="body">
        I mention this because I think you have a right to know how the things you buy are made.
        I would rather tell you up front than have it be a hidden detail.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Fold 6: What you will not find (Bone) -->
  <section class="fold light">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="meta">05 / what you will not find here</div>
      <h2 class="h-mono md">no "adhd is your superpower" content.</h2>
      <ul class="wont-list">
        <li><span class="x" aria-hidden="true">×</span> no clinical advice</li>
        <li><span class="x" aria-hidden="true">×</span> no content that talks down to neurodivergent people</li>
        <li><span class="x" aria-hidden="true">×</span> no promises that a planner will fix you</li>
        <li><span class="x" aria-hidden="true">×</span> no treating us as a problem to be solved</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="wont-tag">tools and humour, that's it.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Fold 7: Thanks + CTAs (Ink) -->
  <section class="fold dark">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="meta">06 / thanks for being here</div>
      <h2 class="h-mono md">i make this for people who get it.</h2>
      <p class="body">
        If you buy something, I see your order. If you message the shop, you are messaging me.
        If a product does not work for your brain, that's information about the product, not about you.
        I am glad you found the shop.
      </p>
      <div class="cta-row">
        <a href="/journals" class="button">shop the journals →</a>
        <a href="https://www.etsy.com/shop/oddlywiredco" class="button outline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">or shop on etsy →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .about-hero { padding-top: 64px; padding-bottom: 64px; }
    .about-hero .container { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 20px; }
    .hero-sub { color: var(--owc-bone); opacity: 0.65; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 16px; max-width: 620px; }
    .body { font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.6; max-width: 680px; margin: 0 0 20px; }

    .pullquote {
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: clamp(18px, 2.2vw, 22px);
      font-weight: 700;
      line-height: 1.45;
      border-left: 4px solid var(--owc-pulse);
      padding: 18px 24px;
      margin: 32px 0 0;
      max-width: 640px;
    }

    /* "what you will not find" — stronger visual moment */
    .wont-list {
      list-style: none;
      padding: 0;
      margin: 28px 0 0;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 14px;
      max-width: 720px;
    }
    .wont-list li {
      display: flex;
      align-items: baseline;
      gap: 14px;
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: clamp(18px, 1.9vw, 22px);
      font-weight: 500;
      line-height: 1.35;
      padding: 4px 0;
    }
    .wont-list li .x {
      flex: 0 0 auto;
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      width: 28px;
      height: 28px;
      background: var(--owc-pulse);
      color: var(--owc-ink);
      font-weight: 700;
      font-size: 16px;
      border-radius: 4px;
      line-height: 1;
    }
    .wont-tag {
      margin-top: 32px;
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 16px;
      opacity: 0.7;
      max-width: 620px;
    }

    /* CTA row — primary filled, secondary outline */
    .cta-row { display: flex; gap: 16px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-top: 28px; }

    /* Subtle Pulse hairline between folds — visual rhythm */
    .fold + .fold {
      position: relative;
    }
    .fold + .fold::before {
      content: '';
      position: absolute;
      top: 0;
      left: 50%;
      transform: translateX(-50%);
      width: 40px;
      height: 2px;
      background: var(--owc-pulse);
      opacity: 0.5;
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
